<item>
            <title>[SOLR-5956] SnapShooter is using getRawInstanceDir, which is sometimes not a valid directory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5956</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Ran into an issue where the getRawInstanceDir method on CoreDescriptor returns an invalid directory on the server. Need to track down where this bad value comes from and fix it. I suspect this has to do with me using symlinks&lt;br/&gt;
e.g.&lt;br/&gt;
I have server with solr.solr.home set to&lt;br/&gt;
/home/ec2-user/lucene-solr/solr/cloud87/solr, which in reality is:&lt;br/&gt;
/vol0/cloud87/solr as /home/ec2-user/lucene-solr/solr/cloud87 is a symlink to /vol0/cloud87&lt;br/&gt;
getRawInstanceDir was returning /vol0/cloud87/demo_shard1_replica1 which is missing the /solr part of the directory path, should be:&lt;br/&gt;
/vol0/cloud87/solr/demo_shard1_replica1&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;SolrCloud&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
