                            <comment id="13959304" author="tim.potter" created="Thu, 3 Apr 2014 22:00:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Quick patch to use getInstanceDir instead of getRawInstanceDir. Be better to track down why getRawInstanceDir is returning the wrong value when using symlinks but this fixes the issue I have now. More later...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14032748" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 16 Jun 2014 18:36:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1602953 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thelabdude&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thelabdude&quot;&gt;thelabdude&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;dev/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1602953&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1602953&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5956&quot; title=&quot;SnapShooter is using getRawInstanceDir, which is sometimes not a valid directory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5956&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-5956&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Use getInstanceDir instead of getRawInstanceDir as that was causing issues when trying to create a backup of an index on Linux when solr.solr.home is a symbolic link.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
